{"title_page": "Epiphanius I of Ukraine", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{short description| 21st-century Metropolitan of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine}}\n{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type  = Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine\n| honorific_prefix = [[His Beatitude]]\n| name  = Epiphanius\n| title  = Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine\n| image  = Epiphany I of the Ukraine in 2019.png\n| caption  = Metropolitan Epiphanius (3 February 2019)\n| native_name  = \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439\n| native_name_lang  = uk\n| church =  [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]]\n| metropolis  = Kyiv and All Ukraine\n| see  = [[Kyiv]]\n| elected  = 15 December 2018\n| enthroned  = 3 February 2019\n| ordained_by  = [[Filaret (Denysenko)]]\n| rank  = [[Metropolitan bishop]]\n| birth_name  = Serhii Petrovych Dumenko <br> \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1979|2|3}}\n| birth_place  = Vovkove, [[Ivanivka Raion, Odessa Oblast|Ivanivka Raion]], [[Odesa Oblast]], [[Ukrainian SSR]]\n| previous_post  = Secretary of the Patriarch of Kyiv and All Rus'-Ukraine [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] (25 January 2008)<br>\nGovernor of the [[Vydubychi Monastery]] (20 March 2008)<br>\nManager of the affairs of the [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church \u2013 Kyiv Patriarchate|Kyiv Patriarchate]] (30 May 2008)<br>\nBishop of Vyshhorod, vicar of the Kyiv diocese (21 October 2009)<br>\nRector of the Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy and governor of the [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] diocese (27 July 2010)<br>\nMetropolitan of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] and [[Bila Tserkva]] and patriarchal governor (28 June 2013)\n| alma_mater  = Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy\n| education  = [[Doctor of Theology]]\n}}\n\n'''Metropolitan Epiphanius'''{{Efn|Also [[romanized]] as ''Yepifaniy'',<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=15148|title= Kyiv Patriarchate does not exist, never existed - Patriarch Bartholomew|date= 3 June 2019|website= www.interfax-religion.com|access-date= 2019-06-03}}</ref> ''Epiphany'',<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14776|title= Metropolitan Epiphany of \"Kyiv Patriarchate\" elected as leader of \"local Orthodox church\" in Ukraine|date= 15 December 2018|website= interfax-religion.com|access-date= 2018-12-15}}</ref> ''Epifaniy'',<ref name=\":0\" /> or Epiphanios.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/ukraine-primate|title=Ecumenical Patriarchate announces election of Metropolitan Epiphanios as Primate of the Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Ukraine|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>|name=|group=}} '''of Kyiv and All Ukraine''' ({{lang-uk|link= yes|\u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439, \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|translit=Epifaniy, Mytropolyt Kyyivs'kyy i vsiyeyi Ukrayiny}}, secular name: '''Serhii Petrovych Dumenko''', {{lang-uk|link= no|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}; born on 3 February 1979) is the [[Primate (bishop)|primate]] of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]] (OCU), holding the title of [[List of Metropolitans and Patriarchs of Kyiv|Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine]].\n\nMetropolitan Epiphanius served as the [[Metropolitan bishop]] of Pereyaslav and Bila Tserkva, in the former original [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church (Kyiv Patriarchate)]] from 2013 to 2018.\n\nHe was a professor of the Department of Biblical and Philological Disciplines of the {{Interlanguage link|Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy|lt=|uk|\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u044f|WD=}}. He was a member of the {{Interlanguage link|National Union of Journalists of Ukraine|lt=|uk|\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|WD=}} and of the [[International Federation of Journalists]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.ua/society/10378467-glava-novoji-pravoslavnoji-cerkvi-v-ukrajini-mitropolit-epifaniy-hto-vin-foto.html|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0457 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439: \u0445\u0442\u043e \u0432\u0456\u043d (\u0444\u043e\u0442\u043e)|last=|first=|date=15 December 2018|website=www.unian.ua|language=uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-23|quote=\u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0454 \u0447\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0421\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0438 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0442\u0430 \u041c\u0456\u0436\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0444\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0457 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432, \u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0436 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u0457.}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSerhii Petrovych Dumenko was born on 3 February 1979 in Vovkove, [[Ivanivka Raion, Odessa Oblast]], in Ukraine. His childhood and school years were in the village of [[Stara Zhadova]] in the [[Storozhynets Raion]] of [[Chernivtsi Oblast]]. In 1996 in Stara Zhadova he graduated from high school of I-III grades.\n\nIn 1996 he entered the [[Kyiv Theological Seminary|Kyiv Theological Seminary]], where he graduated in 1999 with a first class degree. In the same year he entered the [[Kyiv Theological Academy]]. He graduated as a [[doctor of theology]] in 2003 having successfully defended his PhD thesis on the \"Formation of church-canonical collections in the Donician period and their characteristics\".\n\nIn 2006\u20132007 he held an internship at the [[National and Kapodistrian University of Athens|Athens National University]] in [[Greece]] in the Faculty of Philosophy.\n\nOn 30 August 2012, following his successful defense of his doctoral [[dissertation]] on the topic of the \"Doctrine of the Orthodox Church on salvation in the context of the continuity of the Holy Fatherland\", he was awarded a degree of [[Doctor of Theology]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73918/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy (Dumenko) becomes Primate of One Local Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=15 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/administration/rector.html|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432-\u0425\u043c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0411\u0456\u043b\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u041f\u0406\u0424\u0410\u041d\u0406\u0419|website=www.kpba.edu.ua|language=uk-ua|access-date=2019-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218010858/https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/administration/rector.html|archive-date=December 18, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Ministry ==\nFrom 1 July 2003 to 31 December 2005 he served as the secretary-referent of the Rivne diocesan administration and the personal secretary of the [[Metropolitan bishop|Metropolitan]] of [[Rivne]] and [[Ostroh]]. From 26 August 2003 to 31 December 2005 he was a teacher of the Rivne Seminary, and also held the post of senior assistant inspector.\n\nIIn 2003-2005, he led the \"Rivne Pravoslavne\" ({{Translation|Rivne Orthodox}}) [[Internet portal]], and was also a member of the editorial board of the religious newspaper ''Dukhovna Nyva'' ({{Translation|''Spiritual field''}}'')''. In December 2005 he was admitted to the {{Interlanguage link|National Union of Journalists of Ukraine|lt=|uk|\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|WD=}}.\n\nSince the academic year 2007, he has been a teacher at the {{Interlanguage link|Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy|lt=|uk|\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u044f|WD=}}, and was appointed head of the [[philology]] department.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nPn 21 December 2007, with the blessing of Patriarch Filaret, [[Archbishop Dimitriy]] of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytsky]] made Epiphanius a monk in the [[Michael's Golden-Domed Monastery.]] He took the [[monastic name]] '''Epiphanius''' in honor of [[Epiphanius of Salamis|Epiphanius of Cyprus]]. On 20 January 2008 he was ordained [[hieromonk]] by [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]]. Later that month (25 January), he was appointed secretary of the [[List of Metropolitans and Patriarchs of Kyiv|Patriarch of Kyiv and All Rus'-Ukraine]], [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]].<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/vykladatskyi-kolektyv/1849-mytropolyt-pereiaslavskyi-i-bilotserkivskyi-epifanii.html|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0411\u0456\u043b\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439|website=www.kpba.edu.ua|language=uk-ua|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2008 he was ordained an [[archimandrite]] in [[St Volodymyr's Cathedral|St. Volodymyr's Cathedral]]. Later that month (20 March), he was appointed governor of [[Vydubychi Monastery]] in Kyiv.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> On 30 May 2008, he was appointed manager of the affairs  of the Kyivan Patriarchate. On 7 October 2008 he was awarded the title of Associate Professor of the Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy.\n\nOn 21 October 2009, at the Holy Synod of the UOC-KP he was elected Bishop of [[Vyshhorod Raion|Vyshhorod]], vicar of the [[Kyiv]] diocese. On 15 November 2009, he was ordained a bishop.\n\nBy the decision of the Holy Synod of the UOC-KP from 27 July 2010, he was appointed rector of the Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy and the governor of the Pereiaslav-Khmelnytsky diocese. On 17 November 2011 he was awarded the title of professor of the Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy.\n\nOn 23 January 2012, he was promoted to the rank of Archbishop.<ref name=\":1\" /> By the decision of the Bishops' Council of the UOC-KP on 28 June 2013, he was raised to the rank of Metropolitan of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] and Bila Tserkva and was appointed patriarchal governor with the rights of the diocesan bishop.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.cerkva.info/uk/archsobor/3596-arch-sobor-28-06-13.html|title=\u0417\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0410\u0440\u0445\u0456\u0454\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0443 (28 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043d\u044f 2013 \u0440.) - \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442 (\u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f)|website=archive.cerkva.info|access-date=2019-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190104235826/http://archive.cerkva.info/uk/archsobor/3596-arch-sobor-28-06-13.html|archive-date=January 4, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 13 December 2017 he was named [[Metropolitan bishop|Metropolitan]] of [[Pereiaslav]] and [[Bila Tserkva]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cerkva.info/church/zhurnaly-zasidannia-sviashchennoho-synodu-13-hrudnia-2017-r|title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442 (\u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f)|website=cerkva.info|access-date=16 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Primate of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church ==\n[[File:Unification council of Orthodox Church in Ukraine 127.jpg|thumb|Epiphanius, then President [[Petro Poroshenko]] and [[Andriy Parubiy]] on 15 December 2018]]\nOn 15 December 2018, at the [[Unification council of the Orthodox churches of Ukraine|unification council]] held in the [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kyiv|Cathedral of St. Sophia]], he was elected [[Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/world-digest-dec-15-2018/2018/12/15/e7d9f170-0082-11e9-83c0-b06139e540e5_story.html|title=World Digest: Dec. 15, 2018: Ukrainian church leaders approve split from Russians|date=December 15, 2018|website=The Washington Post|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref> the first primate of the [[Autocephaly|autocephalous]] [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://narodna-pravda.ua/2018/12/15/ob-yednavchyj-sobor-u-kyyevi-nazvano-im-ya-golovy-pomisnoyi-tserkvy-v-ukrayini/|title=\u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u041e\u0431'\u0454\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0447\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440 \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u0454\u0432\u0456: \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e \u0456\u043c'\u044f \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456|date=2018-12-15|website=\u041d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zik.ua/news/2018/12/15/predstoyatelem_ukrainskoi_pravoslavnoi_tserkvy_obraly_mytropolyta_epifaniya_1470657|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|website=zik.ua|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.Kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/unification-council-elects-head-of-ukrainian-orthodox-church.html|title=Unification Council elects head of Ukrainian Orthodox Church|date=December 15, 2018|website=Kyiv Post|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/world/ukraine-orthodox-leaders-approve-break-with-russian-church-1.4219567|title=Ukraine Orthodox leaders approve break with Russian church {{!}} CTV News|website=www.ctvnews.ca|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-society/2601704-metropolitan-epiphanius-elected-primate-of-ukrainian-autocephalous-orthodox-church.html|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy elected primate of Ukrainian Orthodox Church|website=ukrinform.net|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/15/world/europe/russia-ukraine-orthodox-church.html|title=Amid Russia Tensions, Ukraine Moves Toward Separate Church|last=MacFarquhar|first=Neil|date=December 15, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=17 December 2018|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nThe official name of the primate the Orthodox Church of Ukraine is \"His Beatitude (name), Metropolitan of Kyiv and all Ukraine\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10378626-kyiv-patriarchate-announces-official-name-of-new-ukrainian-orthodox-church.html|title=Kyiv Patriarchate announces official name of new Ukrainian Orthodox Church|date=15 December 2018|website=unian.info|language=en|access-date=2018-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73930/|title=Official name of new Orthodox Church and title of its Primate, both according to Charter, announced|date=15 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cerkva.info/posts/shchodo-pomynannia-za-bohosluzhinniam-predstoiatelia-pomisnoi-pravoslavnoi-tserkvy-ukrainy|title=\u0429\u043e\u0434\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0456\u043d\u043d\u044f\u043c \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|date=15 December 2018|website=www.cerkva.info|access-date=2018-12-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Commemoration of the Patriarch of Moscow ===\nOn Sunday 16 December 2018, during Metropolitan Epiphanius' first [[Divine Liturgy]] as Metropolitan of the OCU following his election, he called for prayers for peace and unity in Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/new-ukrainian-orthodox-leader-gives-first-liturgy-urging-unity/29659372.html|title=New Ukrainian Orthodox Leader Gives First Liturgy, Urging Unity|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref> In the same liturgy, Metropolitan Epiphany also omitted [[Patriarch Kirill of Moscow]] from the [[Diptych#Ecclesiastical|list of brother primates with whom he is in communion]] who are usually commemorated at the [[Entrance (liturgical)#Great Entrance|Great Entrance]].<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73946/|title=Ukrainian primate avoids commemorating Moscow patriarch in first Liturgy|date=17 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://orthochristian.com/117973.html|title=Displeasure in Constantinople as new Ukrainian primate skips commemoration of Pat. Kirill at Liturgy (+ VIDEO)|date=17 December 2018|website=OrthoChristian.Com|access-date=2018-12-23}}</ref> Metropolitan Epiphanius later explained in an interview with Ukrainian \"Direct\" TV channel: \"At the moment I do not commemorate him [the Patriarch of Moscow] because we are in a state of war, so the Ukrainian people would not accept if the newly-elected primate commemorated the name of the Russian Patriarch.\"<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://prm.ua/eksklyuzivne-interv-yu-mitropolita-epifaniya-na-telekanali-pryamiy-onlayn-translyatsiya/|title=\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432'\u044e \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456 \"\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439\"|date=2018-12-29|website=\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439 \u041e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d|language=en|access-date=2018-12-30}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Citation|last=\u0422\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b \u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439|title=\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u2018\u044e \u0437  \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0454\u043c|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qC6VGTFXWKQ|access-date=2018-12-30}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://prm.ua/pro-protseduru-nadannya-tomosu-sofiyu-kiyivsku-ta-perehodi-do-pravoslavnoyi-tserkvi-ukrayini-epifaniy-u-eksklyuzivnomu-interv-yu-pryamomu/|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0440\u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0443, \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0456\u044e \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438 \u0434\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0443 \u0435\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432'\u044e \"\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e\u043c\u0443\"|date=2018-12-30|website=\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439 \u041e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d|language=en|access-date=2019-01-01}}</ref>\n\nDuring the Divine Liturgy on 7 January 2019, after the OCU received its official autocephaly on 5 January 2019, Metropolitan Epiphanius commemorated the name of Patriarch Kirill during the [[Entrance (liturgical)|Great entrance]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74209|title=Christmas with Tomos: Epifaniy presides over Liturgy at St Sophia in Kyiv|date=7 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74208/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0443 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0456\u0457 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0456\u043c\u0435\u043d \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0456\u0432 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0437\u0433\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0432 \u0456 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0430|date=7 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> Epiphanius later told he had done this after the [[Bartholomew I of Constantinople|Ecumenical Patriarch]] had instructed him to do so, and that [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] had instructed him (Epiphanius) not to mention Kirill.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/features-48233018|title=\u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f: \u0447\u0438 \u0454 \u0440\u043e\u0437\u043a\u043e\u043b \u0432 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0456 \u0449\u043e \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435 \u0437 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043c|last=\u0425\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e|first=\u0412\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0439 \u0427\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e, \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432|date=2019-05-11|access-date=2019-05-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n=== Reception of the tomos of autocephaly ===\n{{Main|Autocephaly of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine#Tomos of autocephaly}}\n[[File:Batholomew handing tomos to Epiphanius.jpg|right|thumb|244x244px|Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew (left) handing the tomos of autocephaly to Metropolitan Epiphanius (right)]]\nOn 5 January 2019, Patriarch Bartholomew and Metropolitan Epiphanius held a liturgy in [[St. George's Cathedral, Istanbul|St. George's Cathedral]] in Istanbul; the tomos of autocephaly of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]] was signed thereafter, still in St. George's Cathedral. The ''tomos'' \"has come into force from the moment of its signing\".<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/constantinople_patriarchy/74166/|title=Patriarch Bartholomew signs Tomos of autocephaly of Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=5 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref><ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74190/|title=Ukraine receives Tomos officially and forever|date=6 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-06}}</ref> The signing of the tomos officially established the autocephalous Orthodox Church of Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.la-croix.com/Religion/Orthodoxie/LEglise-dUkraine-officiellement-creee-patriarche-Bartholomee-2019-01-05-1200993367|title=L\u2019\u00c9glise d\u2019Ukraine officiellement cr\u00e9\u00e9e par le patriarche Bartholom\u00e9e|last=La-Croix.com|date=2019-01-05|website=La Croix|language=fr|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref>\n\nAfter the tomos was signed,  Metropolitan Epiphanius made a speech, in which he declared about [[Petro Poroshenko|Poroshenko]]: \"Your name, Mr President, will forever go down in the history of the Ukrainian people next to the names of the rulers, of our [[Vladimir the Great|prince Volodymyr the Great]], [[Yaroslav the Wise]], [[Konstanty Ostrogski|Kostyantyn Ostrozky]] and Hetman [[Ivan Mazepa]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74172/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439: \u041d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0456\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u0435 \u0434\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e, \u044f\u043a\u0435 \u0437\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0412\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0456\u044f|date=5 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|trans-title=Primate Epiphanius: Our Church will never forget the goodness of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref>\n\nOn January 6, after a liturgy celebrated by Metropolitan Epiphanius and Patriarch Bartholomew, Partriarch Bartholomew read the ''tomos'' of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine|Orthodox Church of Ukraine (OCU)]] and then gave it to Metropolitan Epiphanius.<ref name=\":9\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10400271-ecumenical-patriarch-hands-tomos-of-autocephaly-over-to-leader-of-orthodox-church-of-ukraine-video-photos.html|title=Ecumenical Patriarch hands tomos of autocephaly over to leader of Orthodox Church of Ukraine (Video, photos)|date=6 January 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-01-06}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2019, the tomos was brought back to Istanbul so that all the members of the [[Ecumenical Patriarchate of Constantinople#Holy Synod|Holy Synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate]] could sign the tomos.<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/news-46800260|title=\u0429\u043e \u0437 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u0456\u0434 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0456 \u0447\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0439\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u044e\u0442\u044c \u0434\u043e \u0421\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430|date=2019-01-08|work=BBC News \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref> The ''tomos'' was signed by all members of the synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate on 9 January 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74231/|title=Ukrainian Tomos signed by all members of Holy Synod of Ecumenical Patriarchate|last=|first=|date=9 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10402590-tomos-for-ukraine-church-signed-by-all-members-of-constantinople-synod.html|title=Tomos for Ukraine Church signed by all members of Constantinople Synod|date=9 January 2019|website=unian.info|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref name=\":102\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/archbishop-members-of-ecumenical-patriarchates-synod-sign-public-copy-of-tomos-for-ukraine.html|title=Archbishop: Members of Ecumenical Patriarchate's Synod sign public copy of tomos for Ukraine|date=2019-01-09|website=Kyiv Post|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanarion.blogspot.com/2019/01/blog-post_87.html|title=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 : \u0397 \u03a5\u03a0\u039f\u0393\u03a1\u0391\u03a6\u0397 \u03a4\u039f\u03a5 \u03a4\u039f\u039c\u039f\u03a5 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u039f\u039a\u0395\u03a6\u0391\u039b\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u039f\u03a5\u039a\u03a1\u0391\u039d\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u0391\u03a0\u039f \u03a4\u0391 \u039c\u0395\u039b\u0397 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u0391\u0393\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u0399 \u0399\u0395\u03a1\u0391\u03a3 \u03a3\u03a5\u039d\u039f\u0394\u039f\u03a5|last=Panagiotisandriopoulos|date=2019-01-09|website=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref> The ''tomos'', signed by all members of the synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate, was brought back to Ukraine on the morning of 10 January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/558035.html|title=Tomos returns to Ukraine, brought to Rivne \u2013 Poroshenko|date=10 January 2019|website=Interfax-Ukraine|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14849|title=Tomos returns from Istanbul to Ukraine|date=10 January 2019|website=interfax-religion.com|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1772657-tomos-povernuvsya-v-ukrayinu|title=\u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0432\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0443|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 \u2013 \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/rus/news/2019/01/10/7203434/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f\u043c\u0438 \u0412\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0443|website=Ukrayinska Pravda|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref>\n\n=== Enthronement ===\nIt was planned that Epiphany would be enthroned on 3 February 2019, which is also the date of his 40th birthday.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14871|title=Enthronement of Yepifaniy to be held on Feb 3|date=18 January 2019|website=www.interfax-religion.com|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.ua/rubric-society/2621935-intronizacia-predstoatela-pcu-vidbudetsa-3-lutogo.html|title=\u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f 3 \u043b\u044e\u0442\u043e\u0433\u043e|date=17 January 2019|website=www.ukrinform.ua|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/ogoloshennya-pro-intronizatsiyu-mytropolyta-kyyivskogo-i-vsiyeyi-ukrayiny-epifaniya/|title=\u041e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044e \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|date=2019-01-17|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref> Thereafter, the first synod of the OCU was to take place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://interfax.com.ua/news/general/559923.html|title=\u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0438\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u043a\u0430\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435|date=19 January 2019|website=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441-\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10414518-first-synod-of-new-ukrainian-church-to-be-held-after-enthronement-of-its-head-epifaniy.html|title=First synod of new Ukrainian church to be held after enthronement of its head \u2013 Epifaniy|date=19 January 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-01-20}}</ref> The [[Mount Athos#Administration and organization|monasteries of Mount Athos]] refused to send a delegation for the enthronement ceremony \"not because the [[Monk|Fathers]] do not recognize its legitimacy or canonicity, but because they have chosen to stick with what has become official practice and accept invitations only to the enthronement of their ecclesiastical head, the [[Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople|Ecumenical Patriarch]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxia.info/news/when-fake-news-becomes-an-athonite-craft/|title=When fake news becomes\u2026 an Athonite craft|date=30 January 2019|website=Orthodoxia.info|access-date=15 March 2019}}</ref> Two abbots of Mount Athos were planned to come at the enthronement but were to be part of the delegation of the Ecumenical Patriarchate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/two-athonite-abbots-will-go-to-kyiv-on-february-3-for-metropolitan-epifaniys-enthronement/|title=Two Athonite abbots will go to Kyiv on February 3 for Metropolitan Epifaniy\u2019s enthronement|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-01|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref> On 1 February, once in Kyiv, Archimandrite Ephrem, one of the two Athonite abbots, was hospitalized for a heart attack.<ref name=\":03\">{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/the-abbot-of-the-athonite-vatopedi-monastery-was-hospitalized-in-kyiv/|title=The abbot of the Athonite Vatopedi Monastery was hospitalized in Kyiv \u22c6 Orthodoxie.com|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-02|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref> On 2 February, Archimandrite Ephrem was visited by Epiphanius.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/metropolitan-epifaniy-dumenko-visited-archimandrite-ephrem-in-kyiv/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy (Dumenko) visited Archimandrite Ephrem in Kyiv|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-06|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanarion.blogspot.com/2019/02/blog-post_2.html|title=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 : \u039f \u039a\u0399\u0395\u0392\u039f\u03a5 \u0395\u03a0\u0399\u03a6\u0391\u039d\u0399\u039f\u03a3 \u0395\u03a0\u0399\u03a3\u039a\u0395\u03a6\u0398\u0397\u039a\u0395 \u03a3\u03a4\u0397\u039d \u039a\u039b\u0399\u039d\u0399\u039a\u0397 \u03a4\u039f\u039d \u0392\u0391\u03a4\u039f\u03a0\u0391\u0399\u0394\u0399\u039d\u039f \u0397\u0393\u039f\u03a5\u039c\u0395\u039d\u039f \u0395\u03a6\u03a1\u0391\u0399\u039c (\u03a6\u03a9\u03a4\u039f)|last=Panagiotisandriopoulos|date=2019-02-02|website=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref>\n\nAs planned, Epiphanius was enthroned on 3 February 2019, in [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kyiv|St. Sophia's Cathedral, Kyiv]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10432056-metropolitan-of-kyiv-and-all-ukraine-epifaniy-inaugurated-as-primate-of-orthodox-church-of-ukraine.html|title=Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine Epifaniy inaugurated as Primate of Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=3 February 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] was not present due to health conditions, so he sent his written congratulations to the primate Epiphanius, Filaret's congratulations were written by him and read at the end of the liturgy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://24tv.ua/u_filareta_pogirshilos_zdorovya_i_vin_ne_vidvidav_intronizatsiyu_epifaniya_n1106346|title=\u0423 \u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0433\u0456\u0440\u0448\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044c \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u2019\u044f \u0456 \u0432\u0456\u043d \u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0432\u0456\u0434\u0430\u0432 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044e \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|date=3 February 2019|website=24 \u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b|language=uk|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74575/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 \u043e\u0444\u0456\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0447\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0432 \u041f\u0426\u0423 (\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043e)|date=3 February 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Archimandrite Ephrem, who had been hospitalized on 1 February 2019,<ref name=\":03\" /> was not present at the ceremony of enthronment,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/metropolitan-epifaniys-enthronement/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy\u2019s enthronement|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-07|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romfea.gr/ekklisies-ts/ekklisia-tis-oukranias/26845-enthronistike-o-oukranias-epifanios-binteo|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b8\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03bf \u039f\u03c5\u03ba\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03c6\u03ac\u03bd\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 (BINTEO)|date=3 February 2019|website=ROMFEA|language=el-gr|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref>  but a [[hieromonk]] of Ephrem's monastery was present during the ceremony of enthronment. A monk from a [[skete]] of the [[Koutloumousiou Monastery]] was also present during the ceremony of enthronment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://orthochristian.com/119147.html|title=Despite abbot\u2019s absence, hieromonk of Vatopedi attended schismatic enthronement with abbot of Xenophontos and monk of Koutloumousiou|date=5 February 2019|website=OrthoChristian.Com|access-date=2019-02-16}}</ref>\n\nThe first meeting of the holy synod of the OCU took place on 5 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/vidpovidno_do_statutu-predstoyatel-blazhennishyj-mytropolyt-kyyivskyj-i-vsiyeyi-ukrayiny-epifanij-vyznachyv-sklad-svyashhennogo-synodu-ta-sklykav-jogo-pershe-zasidannya/|title=\u0412\u0456\u0434\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0434\u043d\u043e \u0434\u043e \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0442\u0443 \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c, \u0411\u043b\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0456\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0432\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0438\u0432 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0430\u0434 \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0432 \u0439\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f|date=2019-02-05|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|trans-title=In accordance with the Statute, the Primate, His Beatitude Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine Epiphanius defined the composition of the Holy Synod and convened its first meeting|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/3086/|title=\u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0432 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0454 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0442\u0430 \u0443\u0445\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0432 \u043d\u0438\u0437\u043a\u0443 \u0440\u0456\u0448\u0435\u043d\u044c|date=2019-02-05|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|trans-title=The Holy Synod of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine held its meeting and approved a series of decisions|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref>\n\n== Conflict with Filaret ==\n{{Main|Conflict between Filaret and Epiphanius}}A conflict erupted between [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] and Epiphanius becauses of disagreements concerning the model of governance, the management of the diaspora, the name and the statute of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine|OCU]].\n\nAccording to Filaret, the agreement reached at the unification council was as follow: \"the primate is responsible for the external representation of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church (UOC), and the patriarch is responsible for the internal church life in Ukraine, but in cooperation with the primate. The primate shall do nothing in the church without the consent of the patriarch. The patriarch chairs the meetings of the Holy Synod and the UOC meetings for the sake of preserving unity, its growth, and affirmation.\" Filaret considers this agreement has not been fulfilled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10549452-patriarch-filaret-talks-of-split-schools-metropolitan-epifaniy.html|title=Patriarch Filaret talks of split, schools Metropolitan Epifaniy|date=15 May 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/75797/|title=\u0412\u0456\u0434\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0456\u0434 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0441\u0443 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0443 \u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u044e, - \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445 \u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442 \u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u0432 \u0456\u0437 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043e\u044e|date=15 May 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\n== Academic and social activities ==\n[[File:Secretary Pompeo Meets with Primate of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine Metropolitan Epiphaniy (48947865572).jpg|thumb|Epiphanius with US Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] in 2019]]\nEpiphanius is the head of the editorial board of scientific specialized editions ''Proceedings of the Kyiv Theological Academy'' and ''Theological Bulletin of the Kyiv Orthodox Theological Academy''.{{Citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n\nHe is also an author of more than 50 publications, including several [[monographs]] about Orthodox theology.\n\nEpiphanius is an active religious leader and social activist. He participates in many scientific and educational activities, and has made a significant personal contribution to the development of Ukrainian [[religious education]] and science and the development and strengthening of the [[Ukrainian state]]. He received recognition for this contribution from both the state and the Church in the form of orders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://novynarnia.com/2018/12/13/epifanij/|title=39-\u0440\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445. \u0425\u0442\u043e \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e, \u044f\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f \u0432\u0438\u0441\u0443\u043d\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0443 \u0454\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438|date=2018-12-13|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044f|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-13}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n=== Orders ===\nHe has received the Order of the Holy Apostle and Evangelist John the Theologian, the Order of the Holy Equal-to-the-Apostles Prince Volodymyr the Great of the Third Degree, the Order of the Holy Archangel Michael and the [[Order of the Holy Cross]] of the [[Montenegrin Orthodox Church]].\n\nHe has also received awards and honors with the [[Order of Merit (Ukraine)|Order of Merit]] of \u0406\u0406 and III degrees,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zakon.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/664/2008|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u0456\u044f\u0447\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0443|website=zakon.rada.gov.ua|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zakon.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/670/2015|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0437 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438 24-\u0457 \u0440\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0456 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0440\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0443\u043c\u043e\u043c \u0410\u043a\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043d\u0435\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0436\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0456 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 1 \u0433\u0440\u0443\u0434\u043d\u044f 1991 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443|website=zakon.rada.gov.ua|access-date=2019-01-13}}</ref> a letter of the [[Cabinet of ministers of Ukraine]], thanks to the Prime Minister of Ukraine, a letter of the [[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]], decorations of the [[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|Ministry of Defense of Ukraine]], [[Ministry of Internal Affairs (Ukraine)|Ministry of Internal Affairs of Ukraine]], command [[Army of Ukraine]], with distinctions of the [[National Pedagogical Dragomanov University]] and the Ukrainian People's Embassy.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n2019 Athenagoras Human Rights Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/2019athenagoras-recipient|title=Metropolitan Epiphaniy of Kyiv and All Ukraine to Receive the 2019 Athenagoras Human Rights Award - Archon News Article - Order of Saint Andrew the Apostle, Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|website=www.archons.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/metropolitan-epiphaniy-remarks|title=Remarks of Metropolitan Epiphaniy of Kyiv and All Ukraine on receiving the Athenagoras Human Rights Award - Archon News Article - Order of Saint Andrew the Apostle, Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|website=www.archons.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Academic ===\n[[Honorary doctor]] of the [[National Pedagogical Dragomanov University]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1784946-mitropolit-epifaniy-stav-pochesnim-doktorom-stolichnogo-universitetu|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0441\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043d\u0456\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442\u0443|date=7 March 2019|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 - \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Unification council of the Orthodox churches of Ukraine]]\n* [[Conflict between Filaret and Epiphanius]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\nVideo of the ceremony of enthronment of Epiphanius:\n\n* [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|Radio Liberty]]: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bu9tcgQmK74 LIVE | \u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043e\u0447\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f]\n* ZikTV: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipU3l-A190 \u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f | 03.02.19]\n* \u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yjmBxaqgaXo \u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438]\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-rel|eo}}\n{{succession box\n| title = [[List of Metropolitans and Patriarchs of Kyiv and all Rus' Ukraine|Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine]]  <br/> ([[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]])\n| before = Position established; merging from [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church \u2013 Kyiv Patriarchate]] and [[Ukrainian Autocephalous Orthodox Church]] (see [[Unification council of the Orthodox churches of Ukraine]])\n| after = Incumbent\n| years = 2018\u2013\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Eastern Orthodox Church footer}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:National and Kapodistrian University of Athens alumni]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox theologians]]\n[[Category:People from Odessa Oblast]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian journalists]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian educational theorists]]\n[[Category:Bishops of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church of the Kyivan Patriarchate]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Merit (Ukraine), 2nd class]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Merit (Ukraine), 3rd class]]\n[[Category:Bishops of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Orthodox primates]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{short description| 21st-century Metropolitan of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine}}\n{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type  = Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine\n| honorific_prefix = [[His Beatitude]]\n| name  = Epiphanius\n| title  = Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine\n| image  = Epiphany I of the Ukraine in 2019.png\n| caption  = Metropolitan Epiphanius (3 February 2019)\n| native_name  = \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439\n| native_name_lang  = uk\n| church =  [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]]\n| metropolis  = Kiev and All Ukraine\n| see  = [[Kiev]]\n| elected  = 15 December 2018\n| enthroned  = 3 February 2019\n| ordained_by  = [[Filaret (Denysenko)]]\n| rank  = [[Metropolitan bishop]]\n| birth_name  = Serhii Petrovych Dumenko <br> \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1979|2|3}}\n| birth_place  = Vovkove, [[Ivanivka Raion, Odessa Oblast|Ivanivka Raion]], [[Odesa Oblast]], [[Ukrainian SSR]]\n| previous_post  = Secretary of the Patriarch of Kiev and All Rus'-Ukraine [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] (25 January 2008)<br>\nGovernor of the [[Vydubychi Monastery]] (20 March 2008)<br>\nManager of the affairs of the [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church \u2013 Kiev Patriarchate|Kiev Patriarchate]] (30 May 2008)<br>\nBishop of Vyshhorod, vicar of the Kiev diocese (21 October 2009)<br>\nRector of the Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy and governor of the [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] diocese (27 July 2010)<br>\nMetropolitan of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] and [[Bila Tserkva]] and patriarchal governor (28 June 2013)\n| alma_mater  = Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy\n| education  = [[Doctor of Theology]]\n}}\n\n'''Metropolitan Epiphanius'''{{Efn|Also [[romanized]] as ''Yepifaniy'',<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=15148|title= Kiev Patriarchate does not exist, never existed - Patriarch Bartholomew|date= 3 June 2019|website= www.interfax-religion.com|access-date= 2019-06-03}}</ref> ''Epiphany'',<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14776|title= Metropolitan Epiphany of \"Kiev Patriarchate\" elected as leader of \"local Orthodox church\" in Ukraine|date= 15 December 2018|website= interfax-religion.com|access-date= 2018-12-15}}</ref> ''Epifaniy'',<ref name=\":0\" /> or Epiphanios.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/ukraine-primate|title=Ecumenical Patriarchate announces election of Metropolitan Epiphanios as Primate of the Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Ukraine|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>|name=|group=}} '''of Kiev and All Ukraine''' ({{lang-uk|link= yes|\u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439, \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|translit=Epifaniy, Mytropolyt Kyyivs'kyy i vsiyeyi Ukrayiny}}, secular name: '''Serhii Petrovych Dumenko''', {{lang-uk|link= no|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}; born on 3 February 1979) is the [[Primate (bishop)|primate]] of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]] (OCU), holding the title of [[List of Metropolitans and Patriarchs of Kiev|Metropolitan of Kiev and All Ukraine]].\n\nMetropolitan Epiphanius served as the [[Metropolitan bishop]] of Pereyaslav and Bila Tserkva, in the former original [[Ukrainian Orthodox Church (Kiev Patriarchate)]] from 2013 to 2018.\n\nHe was a professor of the Department of Biblical and Philological Disciplines of the {{Interlanguage link|Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy|lt=|uk|\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u044f|WD=}}. He was a member of the {{Interlanguage link|National Union of Journalists of Ukraine|lt=|uk|\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|WD=}} and of the [[International Federation of Journalists]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.ua/society/10378467-glava-novoji-pravoslavnoji-cerkvi-v-ukrajini-mitropolit-epifaniy-hto-vin-foto.html|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0457 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439: \u0445\u0442\u043e \u0432\u0456\u043d (\u0444\u043e\u0442\u043e)|last=|first=|date=15 December 2018|website=www.unian.ua|language=uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-23|quote=\u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0454 \u0447\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0421\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0438 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0442\u0430 \u041c\u0456\u0436\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0444\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0457 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432, \u0430 \u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0436 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u0457.}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nSerhii Petrovych Dumenko was born on 3 February 1979 in Vovkove, [[Ivanivka Raion, Odessa Oblast]], in Ukraine. His childhood and school years were in the village of [[Stara Zhadova]] in the [[Storozhynets Raion]] of [[Chernivtsi Oblast]]. In 1996 in Stara Zhadova he graduated from high school of I-III grades.\n\nIn 1996 he entered the [[Kyiv Theological Seminary|Kiev Theological Seminary]], where he graduated in 1999 with a first class degree. In the same year he entered the [[Kiev Theological Academy]]. He graduated as a [[doctor of theology]] in 2003 having successfully defended his PhD thesis on the \"Formation of church-canonical collections in the Donician period and their characteristics\".\n\nIn 2006\u20132007 he held an internship at the [[National and Kapodistrian University of Athens|Athens National University]] in [[Greece]] in the Faculty of Philosophy.\n\nOn 30 August 2012, following his successful defense of his doctoral [[dissertation]] on the topic of the \"Doctrine of the Orthodox Church on salvation in the context of the continuity of the Holy Fatherland\", he was awarded a degree of [[Doctor of Theology]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73918/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy (Dumenko) becomes Primate of One Local Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=15 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/administration/rector.html|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432-\u0425\u043c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0411\u0456\u043b\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u041f\u0406\u0424\u0410\u041d\u0406\u0419|website=www.kpba.edu.ua|language=uk-ua|access-date=2019-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218010858/https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/administration/rector.html|archive-date=December 18, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Ministry ==\nFrom 1 July 2003 to 31 December 2005 he served as the secretary-referent of the Rivne diocesan administration and the personal secretary of the [[Metropolitan bishop|Metropolitan]] of [[Rivne]] and [[Ostroh]]. From 26 August 2003 to 31 December 2005 he was a teacher of the Rivne Seminary, and also held the post of senior assistant inspector.\n\nIIn 2003-2005, he led the \"Rivne Pravoslavne\" ({{Translation|Rivne Orthodox}}) [[Internet portal]], and was also a member of the editorial board of the religious newspaper ''Dukhovna Nyva'' ({{Translation|''Spiritual field''}}'')''. In December 2005 he was admitted to the {{Interlanguage link|National Union of Journalists of Ukraine|lt=|uk|\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u043a\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|WD=}}.\n\nSince the academic year 2007, he has been a teacher at the {{Interlanguage link|Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy|lt=|uk|\u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0456\u044f|WD=}}, and was appointed head of the [[philology]] department.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nPn 21 December 2007, with the blessing of Patriarch Filaret, [[Archbishop Dimitriy]] of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytsky]] made Epiphanius a monk in the [[Michael's Golden-Domed Monastery.]] He took the [[monastic name]] '''Epiphanius''' in honor of [[Epiphanius of Salamis|Epiphanius of Cyprus]]. On 20 January 2008 he was ordained [[hieromonk]] by [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]]. Later that month (25 January), he was appointed secretary of the [[List of Metropolitans and Patriarchs of Kiev|Patriarch of Kiev and All Rus'-Ukraine]], [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]].<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kpba.edu.ua/about/vykladatskyi-kolektyv/1849-mytropolyt-pereiaslavskyi-i-bilotserkivskyi-epifanii.html|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u044f\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0411\u0456\u043b\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439|website=www.kpba.edu.ua|language=uk-ua|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2008 he was ordained an [[archimandrite]] in [[St Volodymyr's Cathedral|St. Volodymyr's Cathedral]]. Later that month (20 March), he was appointed governor of [[Vydubychi Monastery]] in Kiev.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> On 30 May 2008, he was appointed manager of the affairs  of the Kyivan Patriarchate. On 7 October 2008 he was awarded the title of Associate Professor of the Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy.\n\nOn 21 October 2009, at the Holy Synod of the UOC-KP he was elected Bishop of [[Vyshhorod Raion|Vyshhorod]], vicar of the [[Kiev]] diocese. On 15 November 2009, he was ordained a bishop.\n\nBy the decision of the Holy Synod of the UOC-KP from 27 July 2010, he was appointed rector of the Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy and the governor of the Pereiaslav-Khmelnytsky diocese. On 17 November 2011 he was awarded the title of professor of the Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy.\n\nOn 23 January 2012, he was promoted to the rank of Archbishop.<ref name=\":1\" /> By the decision of the Bishops' Council of the UOC-KP on 28 June 2013, he was raised to the rank of Metropolitan of [[Pereiaslav|Pereiaslav-Khmelnytskyi]] and Bila Tserkva and was appointed patriarchal governor with the rights of the diocesan bishop.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.cerkva.info/uk/archsobor/3596-arch-sobor-28-06-13.html|title=\u0417\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0410\u0440\u0445\u0456\u0454\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0443 (28 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043d\u044f 2013 \u0440.) - \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442 (\u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f)|website=archive.cerkva.info|access-date=2019-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190104235826/http://archive.cerkva.info/uk/archsobor/3596-arch-sobor-28-06-13.html|archive-date=January 4, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 13 December 2017 he was named [[Metropolitan bishop|Metropolitan]] of [[Pereiaslav]] and [[Bila Tserkva]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cerkva.info/church/zhurnaly-zasidannia-sviashchennoho-synodu-13-hrudnia-2017-r|title=\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442 (\u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f)|website=cerkva.info|access-date=16 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Primate of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church ==\n[[File:Unification council of Orthodox Church in Ukraine 127.jpg|thumb|Epiphanius, then President [[Petro Poroshenko]] and [[Andriy Parubiy]] on 15 December 2018]]\nOn 15 December 2018, at the [[Unification council of the Orthodox churches of Ukraine|unification council]] held in the [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kiev|Cathedral of St. Sophia]], he was elected [[Metropolitan of Kiev and All Ukraine]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/world-digest-dec-15-2018/2018/12/15/e7d9f170-0082-11e9-83c0-b06139e540e5_story.html|title=World Digest: Dec. 15, 2018: Ukrainian church leaders approve split from Russians|date=December 15, 2018|website=The Washington Post|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref> the first primate of the [[Autocephaly|autocephalous]] [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://narodna-pravda.ua/2018/12/15/ob-yednavchyj-sobor-u-kyyevi-nazvano-im-ya-golovy-pomisnoyi-tserkvy-v-ukrayini/|title=\u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u041e\u0431'\u0454\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0447\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440 \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u0454\u0432\u0456: \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e \u0456\u043c'\u044f \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456|date=2018-12-15|website=\u041d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zik.ua/news/2018/12/15/predstoyatelem_ukrainskoi_pravoslavnoi_tserkvy_obraly_mytropolyta_epifaniya_1470657|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|website=zik.ua|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.Kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/unification-council-elects-head-of-ukrainian-orthodox-church.html|title=Unification Council elects head of Ukrainian Orthodox Church|date=December 15, 2018|website=Kyiv Post|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/world/ukraine-orthodox-leaders-approve-break-with-russian-church-1.4219567|title=Ukraine Orthodox leaders approve break with Russian church {{!}} CTV News|website=www.ctvnews.ca|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-society/2601704-metropolitan-epiphanius-elected-primate-of-ukrainian-autocephalous-orthodox-church.html|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy elected primate of Ukrainian Orthodox Church|website=ukrinform.net|access-date=15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/15/world/europe/russia-ukraine-orthodox-church.html|title=Amid Russia Tensions, Ukraine Moves Toward Separate Church|last=MacFarquhar|first=Neil|date=December 15, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=17 December 2018|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nThe official name of the primate the Orthodox Church of Ukraine is \"His Beatitude (name), Metropolitan of Kyiv and all Ukraine\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10378626-kyiv-patriarchate-announces-official-name-of-new-ukrainian-orthodox-church.html|title=Kyiv Patriarchate announces official name of new Ukrainian Orthodox Church|date=15 December 2018|website=unian.info|language=en|access-date=2018-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73930/|title=Official name of new Orthodox Church and title of its Primate, both according to Charter, announced|date=15 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cerkva.info/posts/shchodo-pomynannia-za-bohosluzhinniam-predstoiatelia-pomisnoi-pravoslavnoi-tserkvy-ukrainy|title=\u0429\u043e\u0434\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0456\u043d\u043d\u044f\u043c \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|date=15 December 2018|website=www.cerkva.info|access-date=2018-12-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Commemoration of the Patriarch of Moscow ===\nOn Sunday 16 December 2018, during Metropolitan Epiphanius' first [[Divine Liturgy]] as Metropolitan of the OCU following his election, he called for prayers for peace and unity in Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/new-ukrainian-orthodox-leader-gives-first-liturgy-urging-unity/29659372.html|title=New Ukrainian Orthodox Leader Gives First Liturgy, Urging Unity|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref> In the same liturgy, Metropolitan Epiphany also omitted [[Patriarch Kirill of Moscow]] from the [[Diptych#Ecclesiastical|list of brother primates with whom he is in communion]] who are usually commemorated at the [[Entrance (liturgical)#Great Entrance|Great Entrance]].<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/state/national_religious_question/73946/|title=Ukrainian primate avoids commemorating Moscow patriarch in first Liturgy|date=17 December 2018|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2018-12-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://orthochristian.com/117973.html|title=Displeasure in Constantinople as new Ukrainian primate skips commemoration of Pat. Kirill at Liturgy (+ VIDEO)|date=17 December 2018|website=OrthoChristian.Com|access-date=2018-12-23}}</ref> Metropolitan Epiphanius later explained in an interview with Ukrainian \"Direct\" TV channel: \"At the moment I do not commemorate him [the Patriarch of Moscow] because we are in a state of war, so the Ukrainian people would not accept if the newly-elected primate commemorated the name of the Russian Patriarch.\"<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://prm.ua/eksklyuzivne-interv-yu-mitropolita-epifaniya-na-telekanali-pryamiy-onlayn-translyatsiya/|title=\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432'\u044e \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456 \"\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439\"|date=2018-12-29|website=\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439 \u041e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d|language=en|access-date=2018-12-30}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Citation|last=\u0422\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b \u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439|title=\u0415\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432\u2018\u044e \u0437  \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u043e\u043c \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0454\u043c|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qC6VGTFXWKQ|access-date=2018-12-30}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=https://prm.ua/pro-protseduru-nadannya-tomosu-sofiyu-kiyivsku-ta-perehodi-do-pravoslavnoyi-tserkvi-ukrayini-epifaniy-u-eksklyuzivnomu-interv-yu-pryamomu/|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0446\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0440\u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0443, \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0456\u044e \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438 \u0434\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0443 \u0435\u043a\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0437\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0432'\u044e \"\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e\u043c\u0443\"|date=2018-12-30|website=\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u0438\u0439 \u041e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d|language=en|access-date=2019-01-01}}</ref>\n\nDuring the Divine Liturgy on 7 January 2019, after the OCU received its official autocephaly on 5 January 2019, Metropolitan Epiphanius commemorated the name of Patriarch Kirill during the [[Entrance (liturgical)|Great entrance]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74209|title=Christmas with Tomos: Epifaniy presides over Liturgy at St Sophia in Kyiv|date=7 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74208/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0443 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0456\u0457 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434 \u0456\u043c\u0435\u043d \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0456\u0432 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0437\u0433\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0432 \u0456 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0430|date=7 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> Epiphanius later told he had done this after the [[Bartholomew I of Constantinople|Ecumenical Patriarch]] had instructed him to do so, and that [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] had instructed him (Epiphanius) not to mention Kirill.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/features-48233018|title=\u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f: \u0447\u0438 \u0454 \u0440\u043e\u0437\u043a\u043e\u043b \u0432 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0456 \u0449\u043e \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435 \u0437 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043c|last=\u0425\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e|first=\u0412\u0456\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0439 \u0427\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e, \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432|date=2019-05-11|access-date=2019-05-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n=== Reception of the tomos of autocephaly ===\n{{Main|Autocephaly of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine#Tomos of autocephaly}}\n[[File:Batholomew handing tomos to Epiphanius.jpg|right|thumb|244x244px|Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew (left) handing the tomos of autocephaly to Metropolitan Epiphanius (right)]]\nOn 5 January 2019, Patriarch Bartholomew and Metropolitan Epiphanius held a liturgy in [[St. George's Cathedral, Istanbul|St. George's Cathedral]] in Istanbul; the tomos of autocephaly of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine]] was signed thereafter, still in St. George's Cathedral. The ''tomos'' \"has come into force from the moment of its signing\".<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/constantinople_patriarchy/74166/|title=Patriarch Bartholomew signs Tomos of autocephaly of Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=5 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref><ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74190/|title=Ukraine receives Tomos officially and forever|date=6 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-01-06}}</ref> The signing of the tomos officially established the autocephalous Orthodox Church of Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.la-croix.com/Religion/Orthodoxie/LEglise-dUkraine-officiellement-creee-patriarche-Bartholomee-2019-01-05-1200993367|title=L\u2019\u00c9glise d\u2019Ukraine officiellement cr\u00e9\u00e9e par le patriarche Bartholom\u00e9e|last=La-Croix.com|date=2019-01-05|website=La Croix|language=fr|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref>\n\nAfter the tomos was signed,  Metropolitan Epiphanius made a speech, in which he declared about [[Petro Poroshenko|Poroshenko]]: \"Your name, Mr President, will forever go down in the history of the Ukrainian people next to the names of the rulers, of our [[Vladimir the Great|prince Volodymyr the Great]], [[Yaroslav the Wise]], [[Konstanty Ostrogski|Kostyantyn Ostrozky]] and Hetman [[Ivan Mazepa]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74172/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439: \u041d\u0430\u0448\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0456\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435 \u0442\u0435 \u0434\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e, \u044f\u043a\u0435 \u0437\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0412\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0456\u044f|date=5 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|trans-title=Primate Epiphanius: Our Church will never forget the goodness of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|access-date=2019-01-05}}</ref>\n\nOn January 6, after a liturgy celebrated by Metropolitan Epiphanius and Patriarch Bartholomew, Partriarch Bartholomew read the ''tomos'' of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine|Orthodox Church of Ukraine (OCU)]] and then gave it to Metropolitan Epiphanius.<ref name=\":9\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10400271-ecumenical-patriarch-hands-tomos-of-autocephaly-over-to-leader-of-orthodox-church-of-ukraine-video-photos.html|title=Ecumenical Patriarch hands tomos of autocephaly over to leader of Orthodox Church of Ukraine (Video, photos)|date=6 January 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-01-06}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 January 2019, the tomos was brought back to Istanbul so that all the members of the [[Ecumenical Patriarchate of Constantinople#Holy Synod|Holy Synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate]] could sign the tomos.<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/ukrainian/news-46800260|title=\u0429\u043e \u0437 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u0456\u0434 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0456 \u0447\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0439\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u044e\u0442\u044c \u0434\u043e \u0421\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430|date=2019-01-08|work=BBC News \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0430|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref> The ''tomos'' was signed by all members of the synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate on 9 January 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/en/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74231/|title=Ukrainian Tomos signed by all members of Holy Synod of Ecumenical Patriarchate|last=|first=|date=9 January 2019|website=risu.org.ua|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/politics/10402590-tomos-for-ukraine-church-signed-by-all-members-of-constantinople-synod.html|title=Tomos for Ukraine Church signed by all members of Constantinople Synod|date=9 January 2019|website=unian.info|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref name=\":102\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/archbishop-members-of-ecumenical-patriarchates-synod-sign-public-copy-of-tomos-for-ukraine.html|title=Archbishop: Members of Ecumenical Patriarchate's Synod sign public copy of tomos for Ukraine|date=2019-01-09|website=Kyiv Post|access-date=2019-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanarion.blogspot.com/2019/01/blog-post_87.html|title=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 : \u0397 \u03a5\u03a0\u039f\u0393\u03a1\u0391\u03a6\u0397 \u03a4\u039f\u03a5 \u03a4\u039f\u039c\u039f\u03a5 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u039f\u039a\u0395\u03a6\u0391\u039b\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u039f\u03a5\u039a\u03a1\u0391\u039d\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u0391\u03a0\u039f \u03a4\u0391 \u039c\u0395\u039b\u0397 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u0391\u0393\u0399\u0391\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u0399 \u0399\u0395\u03a1\u0391\u03a3 \u03a3\u03a5\u039d\u039f\u0394\u039f\u03a5|last=Panagiotisandriopoulos|date=2019-01-09|website=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref> The ''tomos'', signed by all members of the synod of the Ecumenical Patriarchate, was brought back to Ukraine on the morning of 10 January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/558035.html|title=Tomos returns to Ukraine, brought to Rivne \u2013 Poroshenko|date=10 January 2019|website=Interfax-Ukraine|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14849|title=Tomos returns from Istanbul to Ukraine|date=10 January 2019|website=interfax-religion.com|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1772657-tomos-povernuvsya-v-ukrayinu|title=\u0422\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0432\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0443|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 \u2013 \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/rus/news/2019/01/10/7203434/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f\u043c\u0438 \u0412\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0441 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0443|website=Ukrayinska Pravda|access-date=2019-01-11}}</ref>\n\n=== Enthronement ===\nIt was planned that Epiphany would be enthroned on 3 February 2019, which is also the date of his 40th birthday.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=14871|title=Enthronement of Yepifaniy to be held on Feb 3|date=18 January 2019|website=www.interfax-religion.com|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ukrinform.ua/rubric-society/2621935-intronizacia-predstoatela-pcu-vidbudetsa-3-lutogo.html|title=\u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f 3 \u043b\u044e\u0442\u043e\u0433\u043e|date=17 January 2019|website=www.ukrinform.ua|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/ogoloshennya-pro-intronizatsiyu-mytropolyta-kyyivskogo-i-vsiyeyi-ukrayiny-epifaniya/|title=\u041e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044e \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|date=2019-01-17|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref> Thereafter, the first synod of the OCU was to take place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://interfax.com.ua/news/general/559923.html|title=\u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430 \u0415\u043f\u0438\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u043a\u0430\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435|date=19 January 2019|website=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441-\u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10414518-first-synod-of-new-ukrainian-church-to-be-held-after-enthronement-of-its-head-epifaniy.html|title=First synod of new Ukrainian church to be held after enthronement of its head \u2013 Epifaniy|date=19 January 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-01-20}}</ref> The [[Mount Athos#Administration and organization|monasteries of Mount Athos]] refused to send a delegation for the enthronement ceremony \"not because the [[Monk|Fathers]] do not recognize its legitimacy or canonicity, but because they have chosen to stick with what has become official practice and accept invitations only to the enthronement of their ecclesiastical head, the [[Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople|Ecumenical Patriarch]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxia.info/news/when-fake-news-becomes-an-athonite-craft/|title=When fake news becomes\u2026 an Athonite craft|date=30 January 2019|website=Orthodoxia.info|access-date=15 March 2019}}</ref> Two abbots of Mount Athos were planned to come at the enthronement but were to be part of the delegation of the Ecumenical Patriarchate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/two-athonite-abbots-will-go-to-kyiv-on-february-3-for-metropolitan-epifaniys-enthronement/|title=Two Athonite abbots will go to Kyiv on February 3 for Metropolitan Epifaniy\u2019s enthronement|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-01|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref> On 1 February, once in Kiev, Archimandrite Ephrem, one of the two Athonite abbots, was hospitalized for a heart attack.<ref name=\":03\">{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/the-abbot-of-the-athonite-vatopedi-monastery-was-hospitalized-in-kyiv/|title=The abbot of the Athonite Vatopedi Monastery was hospitalized in Kyiv \u22c6 Orthodoxie.com|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-02|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref> On 2 February, Archimandrite Ephrem was visited by Epiphanius.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/metropolitan-epifaniy-dumenko-visited-archimandrite-ephrem-in-kyiv/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy (Dumenko) visited Archimandrite Ephrem in Kyiv|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-06|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanarion.blogspot.com/2019/02/blog-post_2.html|title=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 : \u039f \u039a\u0399\u0395\u0392\u039f\u03a5 \u0395\u03a0\u0399\u03a6\u0391\u039d\u0399\u039f\u03a3 \u0395\u03a0\u0399\u03a3\u039a\u0395\u03a6\u0398\u0397\u039a\u0395 \u03a3\u03a4\u0397\u039d \u039a\u039b\u0399\u039d\u0399\u039a\u0397 \u03a4\u039f\u039d \u0392\u0391\u03a4\u039f\u03a0\u0391\u0399\u0394\u0399\u039d\u039f \u0397\u0393\u039f\u03a5\u039c\u0395\u039d\u039f \u0395\u03a6\u03a1\u0391\u0399\u039c (\u03a6\u03a9\u03a4\u039f)|last=Panagiotisandriopoulos|date=2019-02-02|website=\u03a6\u03c9\u03c2 \u03a6\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref>\n\nAs planned, Epiphanius was enthroned on 3 February 2019, in [[Saint Sophia's Cathedral, Kiev|St. Sophia's Cathedral, Kiev]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10432056-metropolitan-of-kyiv-and-all-ukraine-epifaniy-inaugurated-as-primate-of-orthodox-church-of-ukraine.html|title=Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine Epifaniy inaugurated as Primate of Orthodox Church of Ukraine|date=3 February 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] was not present due to health conditions, so he sent his written congratulations to the primate Epiphanius, Filaret's congratulations were written by him and read at the end of the liturgy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://24tv.ua/u_filareta_pogirshilos_zdorovya_i_vin_ne_vidvidav_intronizatsiyu_epifaniya_n1106346|title=\u0423 \u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0433\u0456\u0440\u0448\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044c \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u2019\u044f \u0456 \u0432\u0456\u043d \u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0432\u0456\u0434\u0430\u0432 \u0456\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044e \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f|date=3 February 2019|website=24 \u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b|language=uk|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/74575/|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 \u043e\u0444\u0456\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0447\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0432 \u041f\u0426\u0423 (\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043e)|date=3 February 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Archimandrite Ephrem, who had been hospitalized on 1 February 2019,<ref name=\":03\" /> was not present at the ceremony of enthronment,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orthodoxie.com/en/metropolitan-epifaniys-enthronement/|title=Metropolitan Epifaniy\u2019s enthronement|last=Cazabonne|first=Emma|date=2019-02-07|website=Orthodoxie.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romfea.gr/ekklisies-ts/ekklisia-tis-oukranias/26845-enthronistike-o-oukranias-epifanios-binteo|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b8\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03ba\u03b5 \u03bf \u039f\u03c5\u03ba\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03c6\u03ac\u03bd\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2 (BINTEO)|date=3 February 2019|website=ROMFEA|language=el-gr|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref>  but a [[hieromonk]] of Ephrem's monastery was present during the ceremony of enthronment. A monk from a [[skete]] of the [[Koutloumousiou Monastery]] was also present during the ceremony of enthronment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://orthochristian.com/119147.html|title=Despite abbot\u2019s absence, hieromonk of Vatopedi attended schismatic enthronement with abbot of Xenophontos and monk of Koutloumousiou|date=5 February 2019|website=OrthoChristian.Com|access-date=2019-02-16}}</ref>\n\nThe first meeting of the holy synod of the OCU took place on 5 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/vidpovidno_do_statutu-predstoyatel-blazhennishyj-mytropolyt-kyyivskyj-i-vsiyeyi-ukrayiny-epifanij-vyznachyv-sklad-svyashhennogo-synodu-ta-sklykav-jogo-pershe-zasidannya/|title=\u0412\u0456\u0434\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0434\u043d\u043e \u0434\u043e \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0442\u0443 \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c, \u0411\u043b\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0456\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0456 \u0432\u0441\u0456\u0454\u0457 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0432\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0438\u0432 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0430\u0434 \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0443 \u0442\u0430 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0432 \u0439\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f|date=2019-02-05|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|trans-title=In accordance with the Statute, the Primate, His Beatitude Metropolitan of Kyiv and All Ukraine Epiphanius defined the composition of the Holy Synod and convened its first meeting|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pomisna.info/news/3086/|title=\u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0432 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0454 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0456\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0442\u0430 \u0443\u0445\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0432 \u043d\u0438\u0437\u043a\u0443 \u0440\u0456\u0448\u0435\u043d\u044c|date=2019-02-05|website=\u0404\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430|language=uk|trans-title=The Holy Synod of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine held its meeting and approved a series of decisions|access-date=2019-02-05}}</ref>\n\n== Conflict with Filaret ==\n{{Main|Conflict between Filaret and Epiphanius}}A conflict erupted between [[Filaret (Denysenko)|Filaret]] and Epiphanius becauses of disagreements concerning the model of governance, the management of the diaspora, the name and the statute of the [[Orthodox Church of Ukraine|OCU]].\n\nAccording to Filaret, the agreement reached at the unification council was as follow: \"the primate is responsible for the external representation of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church (UOC), and the patriarch is responsible for the internal church life in Ukraine, but in cooperation with the primate. The primate shall do nothing in the church without the consent of the patriarch. The patriarch chairs the meetings of the Holy Synod and the UOC meetings for the sake of preserving unity, its growth, and affirmation.\" Filaret considers this agreement has not been fulfilled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unian.info/society/10549452-patriarch-filaret-talks-of-split-schools-metropolitan-epifaniy.html|title=Patriarch Filaret talks of split, schools Metropolitan Epifaniy|date=15 May 2019|website=www.unian.info|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://risu.org.ua/ua/index/all_news/orthodox/ocu/75797/|title=\u0412\u0456\u0434\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0456\u0434 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0441\u0443 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0443 \u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u044e, - \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445 \u0424\u0456\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0442 \u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u0432 \u0456\u0437 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043e\u044e|date=15 May 2019|website=risu.org.ua|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref>\n\n== Academic and social activities ==\n[[File:Secretary Pompeo Meets with Primate of the Orthodox Church of Ukraine Metropolitan Epiphaniy (48947865572).jpg|thumb|Epiphanius with US Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] in 2019]]\nEpiphanius is the head of the editorial board of scientific specialized editions ''Proceedings of the Kiev Theological Academy'' and ''Theological Bulletin of the Kiev Orthodox Theological Academy''.{{Citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n\nHe is also an author of more than 50 publications, including several [[monographs]] about Orthodox theology.\n\nEpiphanius is an active religious leader and social activist. He participates in many scientific and educational activities, and has made a significant personal contribution to the development of Ukrainian [[religious education]] and science and the development and strengthening of the [[Ukrainian state]]. He received recognition for this contribution from both the state and the Church in the form of orders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://novynarnia.com/2018/12/13/epifanij/|title=39-\u0440\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445. \u0425\u0442\u043e \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0414\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e, \u044f\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0423\u041f\u0426 \u041a\u041f \u0432\u0438\u0441\u0443\u043d\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0443 \u0454\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438|date=2018-12-13|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043d\u044f|language=uk|access-date=2019-01-13}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n=== Orders ===\nHe has received the Order of the Holy Apostle and Evangelist John the Theologian, the Order of the Holy Equal-to-the-Apostles Prince Volodymyr the Great of the Third Degree, the Order of the Holy Archangel Michael and the [[Order of the Holy Cross]] of the [[Montenegrin Orthodox Church]].\n\nHe has also received awards and honors with the [[Order of Merit (Ukraine)|Order of Merit]] of \u0406\u0406 and III degrees,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zakon.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/664/2008|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u0456\u044f\u0447\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430\u0442\u0443|website=zakon.rada.gov.ua|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zakon.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/670/2015|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 \u0437 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438 24-\u0457 \u0440\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0456 \u043f\u0456\u0434\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u043c \u0440\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0443\u043c\u043e\u043c \u0410\u043a\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043d\u0435\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0436\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0456 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 1 \u0433\u0440\u0443\u0434\u043d\u044f 1991 \u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443|website=zakon.rada.gov.ua|access-date=2019-01-13}}</ref> a letter of the [[Cabinet of ministers of Ukraine]], thanks to the Prime Minister of Ukraine, a letter of the [[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]], decorations of the [[Ministry of Defence (Ukraine)|Ministry of Defense of Ukraine]], [[Ministry of Internal Affairs (Ukraine)|Ministry of Internal Affairs of Ukraine]], command [[Army of Ukraine]], with distinctions of the [[National Pedagogical Dragomanov University]] and the Ukrainian People's Embassy.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n2019 Athenagoras Human Rights Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/2019athenagoras-recipient|title=Metropolitan Epiphaniy of Kyiv and All Ukraine to Receive the 2019 Athenagoras Human Rights Award - Archon News Article - Order of Saint Andrew the Apostle, Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|website=www.archons.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archons.org/-/metropolitan-epiphaniy-remarks|title=Remarks of Metropolitan Epiphaniy of Kyiv and All Ukraine on receiving the Athenagoras Human Rights Award - Archon News Article - Order of Saint Andrew the Apostle, Archons of the Ecumenical Patriarchate|website=www.archons.org|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Academic ===\n[[Honorary doctor]] of the [[National Pedagogical Dragomanov University]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1784946-mitropolit-epifaniy-stav-pochesnim-doktorom-stolichnogo-universitetu|title=\u041c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u043c \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0441\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043d\u0456\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442\u0443|date=7 March 2019|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 - \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Unification council of the Orthodox churches of Ukraine]]\n* [[Conflict between Filaret and Epiphanius]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\nVideo of the ceremony of enthronment of Epiphanius:\n\n* [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|Radio Liberty]]: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bu9tcgQmK74 LIVE | \u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\u0437\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043e\u0447\u0456\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u0426\u0423 \u0415\u043f\u0456\u0444\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f]\n* ZikTV: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipU3l-A190 \u0406\u043d\u0442\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0456\